<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id063e4c1b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s3908"><num value="3908">§ 3908.</num><heading> Technical assistance</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President may direct the appropriate agencies of the United States Government to make available technical assistance to countries seeking to implement the Kimberley Process Certification Scheme.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id063e4c1c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/19/s9">Pub. L. 108–19, § 9</ref>, <date date="2003-04-25">Apr. 25, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/635">117 Stat. 635</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
